His mother recovered enough to be sent home.

00:34:08.480 --> 00:34:10.559
Clark, I just left Tyler in the graveyard.

00:34:10.860 --> 00:34:11.300
Are you okay?

00:34:11.500 --> 00:34:12.880
Heard Whitney talking about his father.

00:34:12.960 --> 00:34:14.099
He said that he could bring him peace.

00:34:15.380 --> 00:34:16.340
Did you call the police?

00:34:19.480 --> 00:34:20.259
Where are you going?

00:34:23.019 --> 00:34:48.679
I need to check out their

00:34:48.699 --> 00:34:49.539
aud maker list.

00:34:49.579 --> 00:34:50.840
Wow.

00:34:51.059 --> 00:34:52.280
As dark as we can get.

00:34:52.340 --> 00:34:52.820
I was looking for the actual contract, told them all that we made money on.

00:34:52.900 --> 00:34:52.920
And before we knew it, Tyler ascended into the graveyard.

00:34:52.980 --> 00:34:53.000
And I told him the whole story.

00:34:53.019 --> 00:34:58.019
Dad, he can't hear you.

00:34:58.019 --> 00:35:01.019
Who are you?

00:35:01.019 --> 00:35:03.019
I've come to help your father and you.

00:35:03.019 --> 00:35:05.019
Hey!

00:35:12.019 --> 00:35:15.019
They can end your pain.

00:35:15.019 --> 00:35:18.019
Know what you're feeling.

00:35:18.019 --> 00:35:26.019
Much it hurts, but I can make it all go away.

00:35:42.019 --> 00:35:44.019
Tyler, don't!

00:35:48.019 --> 00:35:51.019
I heard your friend Clark.

00:35:51.019 --> 00:35:54.019
Seeing his father like this is tearing him apart.

00:35:54.019 --> 00:35:56.019
I can give them both peace.

00:35:56.019 --> 00:35:57.019
It's not your decision, Tyler.

00:35:57.019 --> 00:35:59.019
You're wrong.

00:35:59.019 --> 00:36:01.019
I have to help him.

00:36:08.019 --> 00:36:10.019
You're not taking away their pain.

00:36:10.019 --> 00:36:12.019
You're stealing Whitney's last chance to be with his father.

00:36:12.019 --> 00:36:15.019
You can't stop me, Clark.

00:36:15.019 --> 00:36:17.019
No one can.

00:36:17.019 --> 00:36:18.019
Don't you see?

00:36:18.019 --> 00:36:21.019
I know I can see it in my mother's eyes.

00:36:21.019 --> 00:36:24.019
Your mother's alive.

00:36:24.019 --> 00:36:26.019
She recovered after that night in Metropolis.

00:36:26.019 --> 00:36:29.019
They brought her home to Smallville.

00:36:29.019 --> 00:36:30.019
I thought...

00:36:30.019 --> 00:36:32.019
She's alive, Tyler.

00:36:32.019 --> 00:36:34.019
Let me take you to her.

00:36:48.019 --> 00:36:50.019
It's a miracle.

00:36:50.019 --> 00:36:52.019
It's life.

00:36:52.019 --> 00:36:54.019
As long as we have that, there's still hope.

00:36:54.019 --> 00:36:56.019
She seems so peaceful.

00:37:00.019 --> 00:37:03.019
I thought that I was brought back to relieve the suffering of others.

00:37:03.019 --> 00:37:05.019
But it was my pain all along.

00:37:09.019 --> 00:37:11.019
What if I was the one who brought you back?

00:37:11.019 --> 00:37:13.019
I would have been the one who brought you back.

00:37:13.019 --> 00:37:15.019
I would have been the one who brought you back.

00:37:15.019 --> 00:37:16.019
I would have been the one who brought you back.

00:37:16.019 --> 00:37:18.019
What have I done?

00:37:18.019 --> 00:37:20.019
Tyler...

00:37:20.019 --> 00:37:23.019
I just want it all to be over.

00:37:32.019 --> 00:37:34.019
Tyler...

00:37:46.019 --> 00:37:51.019
I just want it all to be over.

00:37:55.019 --> 00:37:58.019
Interesting choice of location for a meeting, Lex.

00:38:03.019 --> 00:38:05.019
Why didn't you just come up to the penthouse?

00:38:05.019 --> 00:38:06.019
I was making a garbage delivery.

00:38:06.019 --> 00:38:08.019
I didn't want to tarnish the marble.

00:38:08.019 --> 00:38:11.019
I'm not in the mood to joust.

00:38:11.019 --> 00:38:13.019
I was hoping you might explain Dominic's visit.

00:38:13.019 --> 00:38:16.019
My auditors discovered a number of unaccountable

00:38:16.019 --> 00:38:18.019
unaccounted expenditures coming out of the Smallville plant.

00:38:18.019 --> 00:38:20.019
I thought it prudent to investigate.

00:38:20.019 --> 00:38:21.019
Come on, Dad.

00:38:21.019 --> 00:38:23.019
I squandered more on a weekend in Hong Kong.

00:38:23.019 --> 00:38:25.019
You didn't stick your adding machines on me then.

00:38:25.019 --> 00:38:29.019
No, we're talking corporate finances, Lex, not your pocket money.

00:38:29.019 --> 00:38:31.019
It bothers you, doesn't it?

00:38:32.019 --> 00:38:34.019
That I'm not dependent on you anymore?

00:38:34.019 --> 00:38:37.019
That I've made friends in Smallville, people I can trust?

00:38:37.019 --> 00:38:39.019
Don't be ridiculous, Lex.

00:38:39.019 --> 00:38:41.019
I'm happy you're doing well.

00:38:41.019 --> 00:38:42.019
Not even that.

00:38:42.019 --> 00:38:44.019
You're afraid I won't need you anymore.

00:38:46.019 --> 00:38:48.019
I'm not going to be your son.

00:38:48.019 --> 00:38:50.019
You'll always be my son.

00:38:50.019 --> 00:38:53.019
And you will always need me, Lex.

00:38:53.019 --> 00:38:56.019
Aren't you going to ask about Dominic?

00:38:56.019 --> 00:38:59.019
He hasn't checked in for hours, has he?

00:38:59.019 --> 00:39:04.019
Unusual for a man of his tediously predictable nature.

00:39:04.019 --> 00:39:06.019
Go ahead.

00:39:06.019 --> 00:39:08.019
Pop the trunk.

00:39:08.019 --> 00:39:10.019
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

00:39:10.019 --> 00:39:11.019
I'm sorry.

00:39:11.019 --> 00:39:12.019
I'm sorry.

00:39:12.019 --> 00:39:13.019
I'm sorry.

00:39:13.019 --> 00:39:14.019
I'm sorry.

00:39:14.019 --> 00:39:15.019
I'm sorry.

00:39:15.019 --> 00:39:17.019
Pop the trunk.

00:39:17.019 --> 00:39:19.019
Lex.

00:39:19.019 --> 00:39:20.019
What has he done?

00:39:20.019 --> 00:39:22.019
What has he done?

00:39:34.019 --> 00:39:37.019
You want to ask an accounting question, Dad?

00:39:37.019 --> 00:39:38.019
Call me.

00:39:38.019 --> 00:39:40.019
The next time one of your drones bothers the Kents,

00:39:40.019 --> 00:39:43.019
I'll be lucky to catch you right up with a spare.

00:39:45.019 --> 00:39:47.019
If you believe Forschus, you won't regret this.

00:39:47.019 --> 00:39:48.019
Sit here, my dear.

00:39:48.019 --> 00:39:49.019
Here's no way.

00:39:49.019 --> 00:39:50.019
You're sorry to see him around like this.

00:39:51.019 --> 00:39:53.019
Lex?

00:39:57.019 --> 00:39:59.019
Well done.

00:40:07.019 --> 00:40:08.019
Thank you.

00:40:08.019 --> 00:40:13.019
Thank you.

00:40:15.019 --> 00:40:21.019
I twinkle, returning to your eyes.

00:40:21.019 --> 00:40:24.019
I search for you.

00:40:26.019 --> 00:40:28.019
For someone's fire.

00:40:31.019 --> 00:40:36.019
We'll run around this place, stumbling in the dark.

00:40:36.019 --> 00:40:37.019
You all right, Dad?

00:40:37.019 --> 00:40:39.019
Never better.

00:40:39.019 --> 00:40:43.019
And when I feel the skies will never clear,

00:40:43.019 --> 00:40:48.019
you remind me spring is near.

00:40:50.019 --> 00:40:53.019
It's a really nice thing you've done for the Fortnum's.

00:40:55.019 --> 00:40:57.019
Thanks, Mr. King.

00:40:57.019 --> 00:40:59.019
It means a lot coming from you.

00:41:00.019 --> 00:41:02.019
I just want you to know,

00:41:02.019 --> 00:41:05.019
I closed the book on that day at the bridge.

00:41:05.019 --> 00:41:08.019
Why'd you investigate it in the first place?

00:41:09.019 --> 00:41:11.019
That day was a miracle.

00:41:12.019 --> 00:41:13.019
I've never wanted to forget it.

00:41:13.019 --> 00:41:16.019
You're not gonna find out why things like that happen?

00:41:18.019 --> 00:41:20.019
No.

00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:23.019
I just accept the fact that they do.

00:41:25.019 --> 00:41:28.019
You don't need an explanation for everything, Lex.

00:41:33.019 --> 00:41:36.019
How do you get the Metropolis Sharks to do it?

00:41:36.019 --> 00:41:38.019
When your father owns a team,

00:41:38.019 --> 00:41:40.019
maybe it's easier to pull some strings.

00:41:40.019 --> 00:41:42.019
It's strange.

00:41:42.019 --> 00:41:43.019
I never thought Lex even liked Whitney,

00:41:43.019 --> 00:41:45.019
and then he goes and arranges all this.

00:41:46.019 --> 00:41:48.019
I think Lex feels he's become part of our lives.

00:41:49.019 --> 00:41:51.019
I'd like to believe that.

00:41:54.019 --> 00:41:56.019
You asked him, didn't you?

00:41:57.019 --> 00:42:00.019
Being friends with Lex can be complicated,

00:42:00.019 --> 00:42:02.019
but it has advantages.

00:42:04.019 --> 00:42:05.019
What was that?

00:42:05.019 --> 00:42:07.019
Just bring me a hug.

00:42:07.019 --> 00:42:09.019
How you shout and cry.

00:42:09.019 --> 00:42:11.019
How you shout and cry.

00:42:12.019 --> 00:42:14.019
Can't you hear?

00:42:14.019 --> 00:42:15.019
You have to think.

00:42:15.019 --> 00:42:17.019
God, when I'm forever alone,

00:42:17.019 --> 00:42:19.019
can't we just keep crying?

00:42:19.019 --> 00:42:36.019
Oh, you get nervous, dio

00:42:36.019 --> 00:42:41.019
barbara

00:42:41.019 --> 00:42:43.360
I just now want to spend some time with my son.

00:42:47.360 --> 00:42:49.480
My dad and I, we saw each other every day.

00:42:49.480 --> 00:42:51.940
We never really talked.

00:42:55.239 --> 00:42:56.699
I just don't want history to repeat itself.

00:43:00.199 --> 00:43:01.000
That makes two of us.

00:43:11.019 --> 00:43:15.519
Hey, Dad, I think we can catch more fish this year.

00:43:15.519 --> 00:43:17.019
What, new lures?

00:43:17.019 --> 00:43:18.019
Thanks for your vision.

00:43:41.019 --> 00:43:42.099
AUTUMN VENT STEP

00:44:11.019 --> 00:44:41.000
Thank you.

